title: In gear at the Granger: Cowboys produce best finish at Bart Granger Memorial
text:
Photo courtesy of Terry Galbraith COPPELL GOLF 
Coppell’s boys golf team took fifth last week at the Bart Granger Memorial Tournament in Fort Worth. Pictured, from left, are (front): Noah Fuselier, Max Pius and Andrew Lindberg; (back): Coach Kies, Coach Galbraith, Cameron Meyer, Mac Cranmer, Brian Choe and Will Kelly. Posted: Saturday, September 26, 2015 1:19 am In gear at the Granger: Cowboys produce best finish at Bart Granger Memorial Justin Thomas, jthomas@starlocalmedia.com Star Local Media | 0 comments 
For more than a decade, Coppell’s boys golf team has taken part at the Bart Granger Memorial Tournament at Pecan Valley Golf Course in Fort Worth. 
But never has the team returned home with a higher finish that its varsity boys produced in 2015. 
Coppell placed fifth as a team at the event Sept. 18-20, which is widely considered the largest high school event in the nation with more than 250 individuals in action, including a third-place finish from junior Brian Choe. 
The previous best team and individual finishes for the Cowboys were sixth (2005) and fifth (Conrad Shindler), respectively. 
This year, Coppell posted a combined score of 865 (294-285-286), while Choe carded rounds of 72, 68 and 67 for an aggregate score of 207 (5-under-par). 
The rest of Coppell’s scorers included junior Andrew Lindberg in a tie for 16th (213), senior Noah Fuselier in a tie for 45th (222) and juniors Mac Cranmer and Cameron Meyer in a tie for 85th (228). 
Additionally, the Cowboys produced a pair of individual medalists in juniors Will Kelly (56th, 224) and Max Pius (93rd, 229).
